3.20	Ferdinand_Toennies	Ferdinand Tönnies	Ferdinand Tönnies (26 July 1855, near Oldenswort - 9 April 1936, Kiel, Germany) was a German sociologist. He was a major contributor to sociological theory and field studies, best known for his distinction between two types of social groups, Gemeinschaft and Gesellschaft. He was also a prolific writer and co-founder of the German Society for Sociology (of which he was president from 1909 to 1933, when he was ousted by the Nazis).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Ferdinand_Toennies_Bueste_Husum-Ausschnitt.jpg/220px-Ferdinand_Toennies_Bueste_Husum-Ausschnitt.jpg
